# Accessibility Rules

- **Accessibility First**: All code should meet latest WCAG standards
- All interactive components MUST be keyboard accessible.
- Use semantic HTML elements (button, a, nav).
- Use `aria-label` for icons or non-text elements. Don't use `aria-label` for div, span, p elements.
- Ensure focus states are visible.
- Ensure text has a 4.5:1 contrast ratio.
- do not abuse ARIA! according slogan "No ARIA is better than bad ARIA".

  Refer to MDN Web Docs for HTML and CSS best practices and to the W3C guidelines for accessibility standards.
